(secondQuint)Transcutaneous Electrical Acupoint Stimulation(TEAS) for Postoperative Nausea and Vomiting in Laparoscopic Operation.

 Patients were randomly assigned to four groups, receiving TEAS 30 minutes before induction.

The stimulation was applied until the end of the operation.

 Postoperative nausea and vomiting was recorded 30 minute, 2 hour, 6 hour and 24 hour after the operation.

 The adverse events were recorded as well.

